  <body class="- topic/body " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\cinder\vsa\vsa.dita" xtrc="body:1;5:9">
    <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\cinder\vsa\vsa.dita" xtrc="p:1;6:8">This page provides detailed instructions on deployment of HP StoreVirtual Appliance (VSA)
      Storage Nodes, and their configuration as Cinder backend.</p>
    <section class="- topic/section " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\cinder\vsa\vsa.dita" xtrc="section:1;8:14">
      <title id="preq" class="- topic/title " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\cinder\vsa\vsa.dita" xtrc="title:2;9:24">Prerequisite</title>
      <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\cinder\vsa\vsa.dita" xtrc="p:2;10:10">
        <ul id="ul_pfl_bbz_ht" class="- topic/ul " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\cinder\vsa\vsa.dita" xtrc="ul:1;11:32">
          <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\cinder\vsa\vsa.dita" xtrc="li:1;12:15">HP Helion Cloud must be successfully deployed. It should be up and running.</li>
          <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\cinder\vsa\vsa.dita" xtrc="li:2;13:15">Remember to note down the IP address of VSA VM and VSA Cluster from
              <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\cinder\vsa\vsa.dita" xtrc="codeph:1;14:23">~/scratch/ansible/last/my_cloud/stage/info/net_info.yml</codeph> file, which
            is generated by configuration
            processor.<!-- (It is recommended that you write down the IP address so that it can be easily accessible).--></li>
        </ul>
      </p>
      <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\cinder\vsa\vsa.dita" xtrc="p:3;19:10">You can deploy VSA with adoptive optimization (AO) and without adoptive optimization. The
        process to deploy VSA with AO and without AO remains similar except the change in the disk
        input model. For more detailed information, refer to <xref href="#topic_gmc_dgk_jt/deploy-vsa-with-ao-without-ao" format="dita" class="- topic/xref " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\cinder\vsa\vsa.dita" xtrc="xref:1;22:80" type="section"><?ditaot usertext?>VSA with AO and
          without AO</xref>.</p>
    </section>
    <section class="- topic/section " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\cinder\vsa\vsa.dita" xtrc="section:2;25:14">
      <title class="- topic/title " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\cinder\vsa\vsa.dita" xtrc="title:3;26:14">Installing VSA and CMC</title>
      <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\cinder\vsa\vsa.dita" xtrc="p:4;27:10">Perform the following steps to deploy VSA and CMC:<ol id="ol_wgh_djk_jt" class="- topic/ol " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\cinder\vsa\vsa.dita" xtrc="ol:1;27:83">
          <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\cinder\vsa\vsa.dita" xtrc="li:3;28:15">Login to deployer node.</li>
          <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\cinder\vsa\vsa.dita" xtrc="li:4;29:15">Execute the following command to install VSA:
              <codeblock xml:space="preserve" class="+ topic/pre pr-d/codeblock " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\cinder\vsa\vsa.dita" xtrc="codeblock:1;30:26">cd ~/scratch/ansible/next/hos/ansible
ansible-playbook -i hosts/verb_hosts vsa-deploy.yml</codeblock><p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\cinder\vsa\vsa.dita" xtrc="p:5;31:67">Once
              VSA is successfully deployed then you can execute the ansible playbook to install CMC.
              CMC is required to configure the HP StoreVirtual VSA nodes .</p></li>
          <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\cinder\vsa\vsa.dita" xtrc="li:5;34:15">Execute the following command to install
            CMC:<codeblock xml:space="preserve" class="+ topic/pre pr-d/codeblock " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\cinder\vsa\vsa.dita" xtrc="codeblock:2;35:28">cd ~/scratch/ansible/next/hos/ansible
ansible-playbook -i hosts/verb_hosts cmc-deploy.yml</codeblock></li>
        </ol><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\cinder\vsa\vsa.dita" xtrc="b:1;37:17"> Install (any) X Display Tool to Launch Centralized Management Console (CMC)</b></p>
      <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\cinder\vsa\vsa.dita" xtrc="p:6;38:10">You must configure X display tool to launch CMC. User can select <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\cinder\vsa\vsa.dita" xtrc="b:2;38:78">any</b> X display tool.
        In this section we are using <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\cinder\vsa\vsa.dita" xtrc="b:3;39:41">Xming</b> tool as an example to launch CMC. The following
        example provides the steps to install Xming and launch CMC.</p>
      <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\cinder\vsa\vsa.dita" xtrc="p:7;41:10"><!--You must configure X display to launch CMC. Therefore, CMC is required to configure the HP StoreVirtual VSA nodes. In this section we are referring to Xming as a X display tool. The display tool can vary from one user to another.--></p>
      <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\cinder\vsa\vsa.dita" xtrc="p:8;42:10"><!--The follwowing steps provide an example on the configuration of Xming to launch CMC.--></p>
      <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\cinder\vsa\vsa.dita" xtrc="p:9;43:10">
        <!--In order to configure the HP StoreVirtual VSA nodes, you must first install the CMC. The following example provides the steps for installaing CMC. The Xming is a tool we are referring in the example below-->
        <ol id="ol_alr_mdl_jt" class="- topic/ol " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\cinder\vsa\vsa.dita" xtrc="ol:2;45:32">
          <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\cinder\vsa\vsa.dita" xtrc="li:6;46:15">Install <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\cinder\vsa\vsa.dita" xtrc="b:4;46:26">Xming</b> on Windows Box from where you can access the deployer node.</li>
          <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\cinder\vsa\vsa.dita" xtrc="li:7;47:15">Select <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\cinder\vsa\vsa.dita" xtrc="b:5;47:25">Enable X11 forwarding</b> checkbox on the putty session for deployer node. </li>
          <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\cinder\vsa\vsa.dita" xtrc="li:8;48:15">SSH to first control plane node.<codeblock xml:space="preserve" class="+ topic/pre pr-d/codeblock " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\cinder\vsa\vsa.dita" xtrc="codeblock:3;48:58">ssh -X</codeblock></li>
          <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\cinder\vsa\vsa.dita" xtrc="li:9;49:15">Execute the following command:
            <codeblock xml:space="preserve" class="+ topic/pre pr-d/codeblock " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\cinder\vsa\vsa.dita" xtrc="codeblock:4;50:24">/opt/HP/StoreVirtual/UI/jre/bin/java -jar /opt/HP/StoreVirtual/UI/UI.jar</codeblock>CMC
            will be launch successfully.</li>
        </ol>
      </p>
    </section>
    <section class="- topic/section " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\cinder\vsa\vsa.dita" xtrc="section:3;55:14">
      <title class="- topic/title " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\cinder\vsa\vsa.dita" xtrc="title:4;56:14">Creating a StoreVirtual Cluster and adding it to a new Management Group Cluster using
        CMC</title>
      <!--<p><note type="important"><?oxy_custom_start type="oxy_content_highlight" color="255,255,0"?>Ensure that CMC is installed successfully and HP StoreVirtual VSA (one or more) is deployed in the same management network where CMC is installed.<?oxy_custom_end?></note></p>-->
      <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\cinder\vsa\vsa.dita" xtrc="p:10;59:10">Perform the following steps to create the cluster.<ol id="ol_yln_fhl_jt" class="- topic/ol " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\cinder\vsa\vsa.dita" xtrc="ol:3;59:83">
          <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\cinder\vsa\vsa.dita" xtrc="li:10;60:15">Open CMC.<p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\cinder\vsa\vsa.dita" xtrc="p:11;60:27">By default, the CMC is configured to discover the StoreVirtual nodes in
              the subnet in which it is installed. You can manually add the nodes also.</p></li>
          <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\cinder\vsa\vsa.dita" xtrc="li:11;62:15">In the CMC UI, click <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\cinder\vsa\vsa.dita" xtrc="b:6;62:39">Find</b> and then click <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\cinder\vsa\vsa.dita" xtrc="b:7;62:66">Find Systems</b> from the left
            panel. Find Systems dialogue box is displayed.</li>
          <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\cinder\vsa\vsa.dita" xtrc="li:12;64:15">You can choose <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\cinder\vsa\vsa.dita" xtrc="b:8;64:33">Add</b> or <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\cinder\vsa\vsa.dita" xtrc="b:9;64:47">Find</b> option to search the system. Find option
            starts searching for the nodes in the same subnet as that of CMC. Add option displays an
              <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\cinder\vsa\vsa.dita" xtrc="b:10;66:18">Enter IP</b> pop-up box to enter the IP of the StoreVirtual system.</li>
          <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\cinder\vsa\vsa.dita" xtrc="li:13;67:15">In the CMC UI, click <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\cinder\vsa\vsa.dita" xtrc="b:11;67:39">Tasks</b> then point to <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\cinder\vsa\vsa.dita" xtrc="b:12;67:66">Management Group</b> and click<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\cinder\vsa\vsa.dita" xtrc="b:13;67:99">
              New Management Group</b>.</li>
          <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\cinder\vsa\vsa.dita" xtrc="li:14;69:15">In the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\cinder\vsa\vsa.dita" xtrc="b:14;69:25">New Management Group Name</b> box, enter a name for the management group.
            For example: <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\cinder\vsa\vsa.dita" xtrc="codeph:2;70:34">hlm003-vsa-mg</codeph></li>
          <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\cinder\vsa\vsa.dita" xtrc="li:15;71:15">Click <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\cinder\vsa\vsa.dita" xtrc="b:15;71:24">Next</b> to display the Add Administrative User page.</li>
        <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\cinder\vsa\vsa.dita" xtrc="li:16;72:13">Enter the required information (username/password) for the Administrative User.<p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\cinder\vsa\vsa.dita" xtrc="p:12;72:95">For
              example:</p><ul id="ul_cdk_xjl_jt" class="- topic/ul " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\cinder\vsa\vsa.dita" xtrc="ul:2;73:50">
              <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\cinder\vsa\vsa.dita" xtrc="li:17;74:19">username- stack </li>
              <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\cinder\vsa\vsa.dita" xtrc="li:18;75:19">password-stack</li>
            </ul></li>
          <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\cinder\vsa\vsa.dita" xtrc="li:19;77:15">Click <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\cinder\vsa\vsa.dita" xtrc="b:16;77:24">Next</b> to display the Management Group Time page. </li>
          <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\cinder\vsa\vsa.dita" xtrc="li:20;78:15">Add NTP server information and click <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\cinder\vsa\vsa.dita" xtrc="b:17;78:55">Next</b> to display the Domain Name Server
            Configuration page.</li>
          <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\cinder\vsa\vsa.dita" xtrc="li:21;80:15">Skip the DNS and SMTP sections.</li>
          <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\cinder\vsa\vsa.dita" xtrc="li:22;81:15">Click <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\cinder\vsa\vsa.dita" xtrc="b:18;81:24">Next</b> to display a Wizard in the Create a Cluster page.</li>
          <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\cinder\vsa\vsa.dita" xtrc="li:23;82:15">Select the cluster type as <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\cinder\vsa\vsa.dita" xtrc="i:1;82:45">Standard Cluster</i> from the displayed options and
            click <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\cinder\vsa\vsa.dita" xtrc="b:19;83:22">Next</b>.</li>
          <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\cinder\vsa\vsa.dita" xtrc="li:24;84:15">In the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\cinder\vsa\vsa.dita" xtrc="b:20;84:25">Cluster Name</b> box, enter the name of the cluster and click <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\cinder\vsa\vsa.dita" xtrc="b:21;84:90">Next</b>.
            For example: <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\cinder\vsa\vsa.dita" xtrc="codeph:3;85:34">hlm003-vsa-cluster</codeph>.</li>
          <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\cinder\vsa\vsa.dita" xtrc="li:25;86:15">In the Add VIP and Subnet Mask pop-up box, enter the virtual IP and Subnet Mask of the
            cluster in the respective boxes and click <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\cinder\vsa\vsa.dita" xtrc="b:22;87:58">OK</b>. The details are displayed in a
            tabular format in the page. <note class="- topic/note " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\cinder\vsa\vsa.dita" xtrc="note:1;88:47">The VIP IP can be found as the cluster IP value in the
                <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\cinder\vsa\vsa.dita" xtrc="codeph:4;89:25">~/scratch/ansible/next/my_cloud/stage/info/net_info.yml</codeph>
              file.</note></li>
          <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\cinder\vsa\vsa.dita" xtrc="li:26;91:15">Click <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\cinder\vsa\vsa.dita" xtrc="b:23;91:24">Next</b> to go to the next page.</li>
          <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\cinder\vsa\vsa.dita" xtrc="li:27;92:15">Select the checkbox displayed against <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\cinder\vsa\vsa.dita" xtrc="b:24;92:56">Skip Volume Creation</b>.</li>
